                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> The assassin vine detects a creature within 20 feet via @Compendium[pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.Tremorsense]{Tremorsense};</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The assassin vine causes vegetation within a 20-foot emanation to writhe for 1 round, turning this area into difficult terrain. When a creature starts its turn in this area, it must attempt a <span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"20\" data-pf2-traits=\"primal,transmutation\" data-pf2-label=\"Grasping Foliage DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Reflex</span> save. On a failure, it takes a -10-foot circumstance penalty to its Speeds until it leaves the area, and on a critical failure it is also @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Immobilized]{Immobilized} for 1 round. A creature can attempt to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Escape]{Escape} to remove these effects.</p>\n<p>Assassin vines are immune to Grasping Foliage.</p>"
